list.abstract: likely（英 [ˈlaɪkli]，美 [ˈlaɪkli]），英语单词，作形容词时，为很可能的；看上去适合的；有前途的。作副词时，为很可能地。短语搭配有be less likely to do（几乎不可能）。例句为“He was likely to be agreeable.（他很可能会同意。）” likely形容词类近义词有applicable、becoming等，副词类近义词有probably、belike。反义词有unlikely、improbable。

yingyinNormal.en: The metahuman thesis. Yes, the metahuman thesis. More likely than not these exceptional beings live among us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 超人类学说。是的，超人类学说，极有可能的是这些能力超凡的外星人就在我们之中。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, before you react, just listen. You are the most likely candidate at this point. You were distraught, you were drinking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先别激动，听我说。目前你是最有可能的候选人。你当时心烦意乱，还酗酒。

yingyinNormal.en: That doesn't seem likely. Her bed's of sturdy construction. Even the addition of a second normal size human being wouldn't cause a structural failure, much less a homunculus such as yourself.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是不太可能的，她的床的构造很结实，就算多承重一个正常体型的人类也不会引致其床架松动的，更别提像你这样的小雏形人了。

yingyinNormal.en: And every time you didn't meet one of those candidates, everyday that's passed without you calling them, email them, sending them flowers, they will be that much less likely to talk to you next time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当你没有再和那些”可能的对象”见面，日复一日，你没有给他们打电话，没有发邮件，也没有送花，你们进行下一次对话的可能性就越来越小。

yingyinNormal.en: I knew you were likely to take a wife.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就知道你应该会娶妻。

yingyinNormal.en: Better than I deserve, most likely. And you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 比我应得的还要好。你呢？

yingyinNormal.en: That is certainly the more likely to succeed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这样的确应该更有成效。

yingyinNormal.en: Broken. Useless. Likely to cause thermonuclear fission.
yingyinNormal.zh: 坏的，没用，可能会导致热核裂变。

yingyinNormal.en: Could be pneumococcal. Most likely an aggressive flu strain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可能是肺炎球菌，很可能是一种急性流感。

yingyinNormal.en: Are they likely to survive, and so on. And are they?
yingyinNormal.zh: 看看那些庄园是否还能为继。他们能吗？

yingyinNormal.en: And they're also much more likely to have a job in the first place.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且前者在职业上升通道上也具有领先优势。

yingyinNormal.en: For an actionable location, most likely a number of hours. Thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只要目标位置准确，几个小时就行。谢谢。

yingyinNormal.en: Am I supposed to know who that is? Not likely. Veech died six years ago.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你觉得我认识他？不太可能，维奇六年前就死了。

yingyinNormal.en: I bought a ticket from a man who would likely be dead if it wasn't for you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我从一个人手里买了张票，倘若不是你他可能已经死了。

yingyinNormal.en: She pulled a gun on you, Harold. Seems more likely she's a threat to others.
yingyinNormal.zh: 她用枪指着你的头，哈罗德，看上去更像是她对别人有威胁。

yingyinNormal.en: Why not go shopping together? With Mary? Not likely. That was a delicious dinner.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你们一起去吧？跟玛丽吗？不太可能，晚餐真美味。

yingyinNormal.en: In the hot state they would much more likely to see themselves behaving this way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 处于被激发状态时，则发现自己更为可能接受这些行为。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, no, no, no, no. Gavin can't. He already has plans most likely with his mother.
yingyinNormal.zh: 喔，不不不不，盖文没有办法，他已经有计划了，应该是要去看他妈妈。

yingyinNormal.en: So it's likely that I'm related to every Resnick that I ever meet, but I don't know.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以好比我与我遇到过的雷斯尼克都有关系，但我不确定。

yingyinNormal.en: I shouldn't worry, madam. We've likely thrown a propeller blade. That's the shudder you felt.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别担心，夫人，推进器叶片掉了，所以会有震动。

examination_example.sentence: As with any study of this kind, it was unclear if that was the cause — or if breakfast-skippers were just more <highlight>likely</highlight> to be overweight to begin with.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 就像任何此类研究一样，尚不清楚这是否是原因，或者是不吃早餐的人从一开始体重超重的可能性就要大一些。

examination_example.sentence: Those who made breakfast the largest meal of the day were more <highlight>likely</highlight> to have a lower body mass index (BMI) than those who ate a large lunch or dinner.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与吃了大量午餐或晚餐的人相比，那些把早餐作为一天中最f丰盛一餐的人更有可能拥有较低的身体质量指数(BMI)。

examination_example.sentence: "We found that women are doubly vulnerable to marital break-up in the face of illness," Karraker said. "They're more <highlight>likely</highlight> to be widowed, and if they're the ones who become ill, they're more <highlight>likely</highlight> to get divorced. "
examination_example.sentence_trans: Karraker 说：“我们发现，在疾病面前女性易遭受婚姻破裂有着双重原因，她们更容易丧偶，而且如果女性是生病的一方，就更有可能离婚。”

examination_example.sentence: Economic factors seem to explain less of why young adult women are increasingly <highlight>likely</highlight> to live at home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 经济因素似乎不能很好地解释为什么年轻成年女性越来越有可能住在父母家里。

examination_example.sentence: Employed young men are much less <highlight>likely</highlight> to live at home than young men without a job, and employment among young men has fallen significantly in recent decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与没有工作的年轻男性相比，有工作的年轻男性住在家里的可能性要小得多，近几十年来，年轻男性的就业率大幅下降。

examination_example.sentence: For their part, young men (25%) are more <highlight>likely</highlight> than young women (19%) to be living in the home of another family member, a non-relative or in some type of group quarters.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 至于年轻男性(25%)，相较年轻女性(19%)，他们更可能住在其他家庭成员或非亲属家，或是住在某种集体宿舍。

examination_example.sentence: Adults ages 18 to 34 were slightly more <highlight>likely</highlight> to be living in their parents'home than they were to be living with a spouse or partner in their own household.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 18岁到34岁的成年人“住在父母家的可能性”首次略超“和配偶或伴侣住在自己家的可能性”。

examination_example.sentence: In addition, trends in both employment status and wages have <highlight>likely</highlight> contributed to the growing share of young adults who are living in the home of their parent (s) , and this is especially true of young men.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 此外，就业状况和工资的趋势可能也是导致住在父母家里的年轻人的比例不断增加的原因，这一点在年轻男性中尤其如此。

examination_example.sentence: In general, the study found that undergraduates were almost as <highlight>likely</highlight> as old people to make this mistake and men as <highlight>likely</highlight> as women.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 总的来说，研究发现，大学生几乎和老人一样会犯这个错误，男人和女人犯错概率也一样。

examination_example.sentence: It seems <highlight>likely</highlight>, then, that the traditional three-stage life will evolve into multiple stages containing two, three, or even more different careers. Each of these stages could potentially be different.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那么，传统的三段式生活似乎很可能演变成包含两个、三个甚至更多不同职业生涯的多个生命阶段。每个阶段可能各不相同。

examination_example.sentence: James Bentham, a co-author of the research from Imperial College, London, says the global trend is <highlight>likely</highlight> to be due primarily to improvements in nutrition and healthcare.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 来自伦敦帝国理工学院的研究报告合著者 James Bentham 表示，这一全球趋势可能主要是由于营养和医疗保健的改善。

examination_example.sentence: This is mainly because women are more <highlight>likely</highlight> than men to be single parents living with their children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这主要是因为女性比男性更有可能成为带孩子一起生活的单亲父母。

examination_example.sentence: While the study didn't assess why divorce in more <highlight>likely</highlight> when wives but not husbands become seriously ill, Karraker offers a few possible reasons.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然这项研究并未对妻子(而非丈夫)患病时离婚概率更高的原因做出评定，但 Karraker 提供了几个可能的原因。

examination_example.sentence: While they sound efficient and cost-saving, a recent study reports that they are not effective, primarily because depressed patients are not <highlight>likely</highlight> to engage with them or stick with them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然这些线上项目听起来既高效又节省成本，但最近的一项研究表明事实并非如此，主要因为抑郁症患者不太可能配合参与或者一直坚持下去。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 从联邦调查局(FBI)告诉我们的情况来看，它被记录为失踪，很可能是被一个实习生拿走的。
